<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-21T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="472" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2376: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-21T19:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            21, 1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 21, 1.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Asia Banking Corporation has made a contract for a loan of $500,000
                                with the Hupeh Provincial Government, with Central Government
                                sanction and guarantee security income of provincial mint, purpose
                                not stated. Japanese bank claims option [on] all Hupeh loans.
                                Provincial Government considers Japanese terms too high. Should the
                                Legation approve?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>